#N canvas 50 50 1180 900 10;
#X text 20 15 pickup.pd v2 - NES Pulse 1 + Pulse 2 with controllable duty + pitch sweep;
#X text 20 40 Listens for: /unity/trigger (int 0-8 = semitone offset in C major scale);
#X text 20 65 Outputs: audio signal (mono) via [outlet~];
#X text 20 100 INTERNAL CONTROL BUSES (set from MockMidterm.pd \, defaulted via loadbang on right):;
#X text 30 125 pickup_duty1 : Pulse 1 duty cycle (0-1 \, default 0.5 = 50% square);
#X text 30 147 pickup_duty2 : Pulse 2 duty cycle (0-1 \, default 0.25 = 25% pulse);
#X text 30 169 pickup_sweep_amt : pitch sweep in semitones (-12 to 12 \, default 0 = no sweep);
#X text 30 191 pickup_sweep_time : sweep duration in ms (10-200 \, default 30);
#X text 20 225 TECHNIQUES (NES-authentic):;
#X text 30 250 - [phasor~] -> [expr~ if($v1 < $v2 \, 1 \, -1)] = bipolar pulse wave with variable duty;
#X text 30 272 - Pulse 2 sits a perfect fifth above Pulse 1 (* 1.5) for chordal NES feel;
#X text 30 294 - Pitch sweep is a [vline~] in semitones added to note signal BEFORE [mtof~];
#X text 30 316 - Sum -> [*~ 0.5] gain -> [hip~ 5] DC-block -> [vline~] amp envelope -> [outlet~];
#X obj 60 350 r osctrig;
#X obj 60 385 select 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8;
